cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CY 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to classify relationships between sentences in legal court case transcripts. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves the use of machine learning models, which suggests that it could be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with information retrieval, which could classify it under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper involves the legal domain, which could classify it under cs.CY (Computers and Society).
